# Fix: Beta Features Not Working

## Root Cause Summary

All broken features stem from two bugs in [server/index.js](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js):

**Bug 1: Lock Screen / Shutdown / Focus App — broadcast to `undefined`**

The server handlers for `trigger-lock-screen`, `trigger-shutdown`, and `trigger-focus` expect a `targetSocketId` parameter to know which students to target. However, the teacher's client only sends `{classId}` (no `targetSocketId`), so `io.to(undefined)` is called — broadcasting to nobody.

**Bug 2: [getTeacherClassId](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js#2758-2766) and [getUserClassId](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js#2749-2757) are undefined**

The monitoring handlers (`start-monitoring`, `stop-monitoring`, `request-high-res-frame`, `monitoring-frame`) call two helper functions ([getTeacherClassId(socketId)](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js#2758-2766) and [getUserClassId(socketId)](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js#2749-2757)) that **don't exist anywhere in [server/index.js](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js)**. This causes a `ReferenceError` that silently swallows the event, so students never receive the monitoring command and the teacher never receives screenshot frames.

## Proposed Changes

### Server — [server/index.js](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js)

#### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/server/index.js)

**Change 1: Add missing helper functions** (before the `io.on('connection', ...)` block)

Add two helper functions that scan `activeClasses` to find a class by socket ID:
```js
// Find the class a teacher is currently managing
function getTeacherClassId(socketId) {
    for (const [classId, data] of activeClasses.entries()) {
        if (data.teacherId === socketId) return classId;
    }
    return null;
}
// Find the class any user (teacher or student) currently belongs to
function getUserClassId(socketId) {
    for (const [classId, data] of activeClasses.entries()) {
        if (data.users.some(u => u.id === socketId)) return classId;
    }
    return null;
}
```

**Change 2: Fix `trigger-lock-screen` handler** (lines 1471-1478)

When `targetSocketId` is omitted, broadcast `execute-lock-screen` to **all students** in the class.

```js
socket.on('trigger-lock-screen', ({ classId, targetSocketId }) => {
    if (!activeClasses.has(classId)) return;
    const classData = activeClasses.get(classId);
    if (classData.teacherId !== socket.id) return;
    if (targetSocketId) {
        io.to(targetSocketId).emit('execute-lock-screen');
    } else {
        // Broadcast to all students in the class
        classData.students.forEach(s => io.to(s.id).emit('execute-lock-screen'));
    }
});
```

**Change 3: Fix `trigger-shutdown` handler** (lines 1480-1487) — same pattern

```js
socket.on('trigger-shutdown', ({ classId, targetSocketId }) => {
    if (!activeClasses.has(classId)) return;
    const classData = activeClasses.get(classId);
    if (classData.teacherId !== socket.id) return;
    if (targetSocketId) {
        io.to(targetSocketId).emit('execute-shutdown');
    } else {
        classData.students.forEach(s => io.to(s.id).emit('execute-shutdown'));
    }
});
```

**Change 4: Fix `trigger-focus` handler** (lines 1489-1496) — same pattern

```js
socket.on('trigger-focus', ({ classId, targetSocketId }) => {
    if (!activeClasses.has(classId)) return;
    const classData = activeClasses.get(classId);
    if (classData.teacherId !== socket.id) return;
    if (targetSocketId) {
        io.to(targetSocketId).emit('execute-focus');
    } else {
        classData.students.forEach(s => io.to(s.id).emit('execute-focus'));
    }
});
```

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (requires two ClassSend instances or teacher + at least one student)

1. **Lock Screen**: Teacher clicks the lock screen button → all student PCs should lock immediately.
2. **Focus App**: Teacher clicks Focus App → all student ClassSend windows should come to the foreground.
3. **End of Day**: Teacher clicks the shutdown button → confirms warning dialog → all student PCs shut down.
4. **Student Monitoring**: Teacher enables monitoring in settings → opens Class Status view — student screen thumbnails should appear and refresh.
5. **Auto-Download**: Teacher enables auto-download and sets path to `[Downloads]` → student receives a shared file → file auto-saves to student's Downloads folder.

> [!NOTE]
> Lock Screen and Shutdown will trigger real OS actions on student PCs. Test in a controlled environment.
